definition.value: a hospitalization AE that leads to a prolonged hospitalization.
an adverse event that occurs locally in a certain location. This is different from the systematci adverse event that occurs throughout the systemtic circulation.

label.value: obsolete: injury or procedural complication AE

definition.value: an adverse event that shows a result of injury or procedural complication.
3/11/2019: This term became obsolete since the "or" structure is confusing, and injury AE and procedure complication AE are two different categories.
a nervous system AE that occurs in the central nervous system
a nervous system AE that occurs in the area of meninges
an inflammation AE which has an outcome of brain inflammation, which is local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes in the brain
a mental disorder that has false personal beliefs held contrary to reality, despite contradictory evidence and common sense.
an inflammation AE that has an inflammation involving the larynx.
a male reproductive system AE that has involvement of the testis.
an urinary system AE that has  urination at short intervals.
a reproduction system inflammation AE that has inflammation involving the vagina. Symptoms may include redness, edema, marked discomfort and an increase in vaginal discharge.
a cranial neuropathy AE that has  involvement of the trigeminal nerve (fifth cranial nerve).
cranial neuropathy AE that has  involvement of the accessory nerve (eleventh cranial nerve).
a cranial neuropathy AE that has  involvement of the hypoglossal nerve (twelfth cranial nerve).
a hemorrhage AE that has  bleeding from the pharynx.
a distal neuropathy AE that has  regional paresthesia of the brachial plexus, marked discomfort and muscle weakness, and limited movement in the arm or hand.
a cranial neuropathy AE that has  involvement of the acoustic nerve (eighth cranial nerve)
a cranial neuropathy AE that has  involvement of the olfactory nerve (first cranial nerve).
a cranial neuropathy AE that has  involvement of the glossopharyngeal nerve (ninth cranial nerve).
a cranial neuropathy AE that has  involvement of the vagus nerve (tenth cranial nerve).
a cranial neuropathy AE that has  involvement of the abducens nerve (sixth cranial nerve).
a cranial neuropathy AE that has  involvement of the facial nerve (seventh cranial nerve).
a cranial neuropathy AE that has  involvement of the oculomotor nerve (third cranial nerve).
a sensory neuropathy AE that has  distortion of sensory perception, resulting in an abnormal and unpleasant sensation.
a pain AE that has  painful or difficult coitus.
a bone disorder AE that has  non-neoplastic overgrowth of bone.
an endocrine system AE that has  excessive development of the breasts in males.
a brain edema AE that has  an abnormal increase of cerebrospinal fluid in the ventricles of the brain.
an edema AE that has excessive fluid collection in tissues that causes swelling.
a menstrual disorder AE that has  the permanent cessation of menses, usually defined by 12 consecutive months of amenorrhea in a woman over 45 years of age.
a physical examination result abnormal AE that is having a high amount of body fat.
a lung inflammation AE that has progressive and life-threatening pulmonary distress in the absence of an underlying pulmonary condition, usually following major trauma or surgery.

a cardiovascular AE that has obstruction of the blood flow in the superior vena cava. Signs and symptoms include swelling and cyanosis of the face, neck, and upper arms, cough, orthopnea and headache.
a menstrual disorder AE that has abnormally painful abdominal cramps during menses.
a behavior and neurological AE that has an exaggerated feeling of well-being which is disproportionate to events and stimuli.
a pain AE that has marked discomfort sensation on the lateral side of the body in the region below the ribs and above the hip.
a metabolic disorder AE that has  an inability to properly metabolize glucose.
a urine abnormality AE that has laboratory test results that indicate the presence of free hemoglobin in the urine.
a sweating AE that has reduced sweating.
a bone disorder AE that has  an abnormal increase in the curvature of the thoracic portion of the spine.
a bone disorder AE that has  an abnormal increase in the curvature of the lumbar portion of the spine.
a male reproductive system AE that has a decrease in the number of spermatozoa in the semen.

a necrosis AE that has  necrotic changes in the bone tissue due to interruption of blood supply. Most often affecting the epiphysis of the long bones, the necrotic changes result in the collapse and the destruction of the bone structure.
an inflammation AE that has inflammation of the skin characterized by the presence of bullae which are filled with fluid.
a speech disorder AE that has  impairment of verbal communication skills, often resulting from brain damage.
a female reproductive system AE that has a narrowing of the vaginal canal.
a metabolism, endocrine, and exocrine system AE that has abnormally high alkalinity (low hydrogen-ion concentration) of the blood and other body tissues.
a gastrointestinal disorder AE that has  repeated gulp sounds that result from an involuntary opening and closing of the glottis. This is attributed to a spasm of the diaphragm.
an urine abnormality AE that has  laboratory test results that indicate the presence of excessive protein in the urine. It is predominantly albumin, but also globulin.
an inflammation AE that has  generalized inflammatory erythema and exfoliation. The inflammatory process involves > 90% of the body surface area.
